  "id": "CENTRAL-EMP-COMP",
  "name": "Employees' Compensation Act, 1923",
  "shortName": "Employees' Compensation Act",
  "officialCitation": "The Employee's Compensation Act, 1923 (Act No. 8 of 1923), repealed and saved under section 164 of the Code on Social Security, 2020.",
  "overview": "Historical central labour-law record governing employer liability to pay compensation for employment injury, occupational disease, disablement or death before the Code on Social Security, 2020 became operative on 21 November 2025. The Employee's Compensation Act, 1923 was repealed by section 164 of the Code on Social Security, 2020, subject to the statutory savings and transitional provisions. Current employees' compensation obligations must be evaluated under Chapter VII of the Code on Social Security, 2020 and the applicable Central or State rules and notifications. This record is retained for historical periods, saved claims, pending proceedings, legacy actions and audit traceability.",
